{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.20",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 20 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:1",
      "text": "Then Zophar the Naamathite answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:2",
      "text": "“Therefore my thoughts answer me, even by reason of my haste that is in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:3",
      "text": "I have heard the reproof which puts me to shame. The spirit of my understanding answers me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:4",
      "text": "Don’t you know this from old time, since man was placed on earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:5",
      "text": "that the triumphing of the wicked is short, the joy of the godless but for a moment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:6",
      "text": "Though his height mount up to the heavens, and his head reach to the clouds,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:7",
      "text": "yet he will perish forever like his own dung. Those who have seen him will say, ‘Where is he?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:8",
      "text": "He will fly away as a dream, and will not be found. Yes, he will be chased away like a vision of the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:9",
      "text": "The eye which saw him will see him no more, neither will his place see him any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:10",
      "text": "His children will seek the favor of the poor. His hands will give back his wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:11",
      "text": "His bones are full of his youth, but youth will lie down with him in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:12",
      "text": "“Though wickedness is sweet in his mouth, though he hide it under his tongue,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:13",
      "text": "though he spare it, and will not let it go, but keep it still within his mouth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:14",
      "text": "yet his food in his bowels is turned. It is cobra venom within him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:15",
      "text": "He has swallowed down riches, and he will vomit them up again. God will cast them out of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:16",
      "text": "He will suck cobra venom. The viper’s tongue will kill him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:17",
      "text": "He will not look at the rivers, the flowing streams of honey and butter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:18",
      "text": "He will restore that for which he labored, and will not swallow it down. He will not rejoice according to the substance that he has gotten.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:19",
      "text": "For he has oppressed and forsaken the poor. He has violently taken away a house, and he will not build it up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:20",
      "text": "“Because he knew no quietness within him, he will not save anything of that in which he delights.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:21",
      "text": "There was nothing left that he didn’t devour, therefore his prosperity will not endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:22",
      "text": "In the fullness of his sufficiency, distress will overtake him. The hand of everyone who is in misery will come on him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:23",
      "text": "When he is about to fill his belly, God will cast the fierceness of his wrath on him. It will rain on him while he is eating.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:24",
      "text": "He will flee from the iron weapon. The bronze arrow will strike him through.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:25",
      "text": "He draws it out, and it comes out of his body. Yes, the glittering point comes out of his liver. Terrors are on him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:26",
      "text": "All darkness is laid up for his treasures. An unfanned fire will devour him. It will consume that which is left in his tent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:27",
      "text": "The heavens will reveal his iniquity. The earth will rise up against him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:28",
      "text": "The increase of his house will depart. They will rush away in the day of his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.20.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:29",
      "text": "This is the portion of a wicked man from God, the heritage appointed to him by God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
